[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://ai/ai_profile.gd" id="1"]

; Easy. Bad judgement, never a handicap: the same income, vision and dice as
; every other tier — it simply reads the board worse.
;
; threat_aversion is the timidity dial, turned the opposite way from Difficult's.
; The DF4 ladder found that over-weighting danger is what actually makes this
; planner weak (0.5 alone loses 88% of its games), and "flinches from danger" is
; exactly the character Easy wants: it hangs back, refuses trades it should take,
; and lets the player dictate the fight. The remaining weights say the rest —
; poor finishing, fears every counter, runs home early, shrugs at marginal plays,
; over-buys infantry, and never fields an md tank.
